I was thinking of another idea for the Gating rollout.
Since the current soft gate is easy to overlook, many teams may not realize they're already failing the VSaaS gate. Rather than starting with hard gating in UAT/Production, could we explore using the Gating Service to enforce the gate in the Dev environment only?
If the VSaaS gate fails in Dev, developers would receive a clear warning and could auto-approve the deployment to continue. This would make teams aware that they're failing the gate today while avoiding any impact to higher environments. It also gives them time to remediate issues (such as Image Age) before hard gating is introduced in UAT/Production.
It might be a good middle ground between today's soft gating, which is often ignored, and full hard gating in higher environments. Just a thought.
